1
00:00:00,830 --> 00:00:03,190
On the fourth day of the Grand Magic Games,

2
00:00:03,190 --> 00:00:05,410
in one of the battle part's tag matches,

3
00:00:05,410 --> 00:00:09,650
a showdown between four 
Dragon Slayers is happening.

4
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:14,990
It's Natsu and Gajeel vs. Sting and Rogue.

5
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:18,030
The battle against the Twin 
Dragons of Sabertooth,

6
00:00:18,030 --> 00:00:24,710
a battle that puts Fairy Tail's bond and 
pride on the line, has begun at last!

7
00:01:55,570 --> 00:01:57,170
Clam it, already!

8
00:01:57,860 --> 00:02:00,190
Wha...?! Hey! You bastard!

9
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:01,830
Wh-What is this?!

10
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:12,000
I can take both of you on by myself.

11
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,170
Go ahead, attack me at the same time!

12
00:02:14,170 --> 00:02:18,390
Oh, boy! Now Natsu Dragneel of Fairy Tail

13
00:02:18,390 --> 00:02:21,970
is challenging the two of them to a battle!

14
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:24,320
You're fired up, ain'tcha?

15
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,700
Natsu vs. the Twin Dragons!

16
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Go, Natsu!

17
00:02:32,510 --> 00:02:34,190
What happened to Gajeel?!

18
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:36,390
Gray-sama! You're wonderful!

19
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,470
Although Natsu is the one who's fighting...

20
00:02:39,170 --> 00:02:40,540
Rogue...

21
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:44,410
Sting-kun! The fight's just getting started!

22
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:01,240
This is...

23
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:03,070
Him?!

24
00:03:03,070 --> 00:03:05,020
It feels like Zeref,

25
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,120
but it's different somehow.

26
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:10,660
He's in the stadium again, isn't he?

27
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,790
Jellal! Don't let him get away this time!

28
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:18,360
I know! I'm concerned about 
the match, but right now...

29
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,150
You can take us on by yourself?

30
00:03:21,550 --> 00:03:23,350
You're just messin' with us...

31
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:25,530
I have no business with you.

32
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:27,930
Let me fight Gajeel.

33
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:30,700
You want Gajeel, you gotta go through me.

34
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:36,320
Dragon Force is the power of a dragon.

35
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:40,320
There's nothing more powerful in this world!

36
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:48,050
Maybe your power's half-baked...

37
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:56,710
Natsu...

38
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:59,160
I wonder what's happening with the match...

39
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:01,500
Natsu and Gajeel are winnin', of course!

40
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:02,970
They're Men!

41
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:05,460
I understand if you're worried,

42
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:08,140
but it's your job to rest up

43
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:10,870
and regain your strength and magic.

44
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:12,270
But...

45
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:15,230
Knowing Natsu-san, I'm 
sure he'll be fine, right?

46
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,030
Gajeel, too...

47
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:22,330
They're so tough, they should have a plaque 
with that word hanging on a wall, right?

48
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,570
That's right!

49
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:27,550
Now you're talking!

50
00:04:27,550 --> 00:04:30,220
That's Carla for you! You're a Man!

51
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:32,710
No, I'm a girl!

52
00:04:34,370 --> 00:04:35,670
These people...

53
00:04:35,670 --> 00:04:38,030
My power is complete!

54
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:42,060
This is the power I used to kill Vicelogia!

55
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:47,400
I see. Then I'll use my power...

56
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,990
...to fight for my friends 
who were laughed at.

57
00:05:03,490 --> 00:05:04,530
Look out, Natsu!

58
00:05:04,530 --> 00:05:05,780
Behind you!

59
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:09,180
Roar of the Shadow Dragon!

60
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:12,390
Roar of the Fire Dragon!

61
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:20,890
That was nothing!

62
00:05:21,770 --> 00:05:23,280
Frosch...

63
00:05:23,730 --> 00:05:24,950
I...

64
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:27,440
I can still fight!

65
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,680
Bring it on.

66
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:35,410
Yeesh. That guy...

67
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:37,920
Look at that gleeful mug...

68
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:40,990
Those two definitely aren't weak,

69
00:05:40,990 --> 00:05:47,860
but Natsu responds to stronger opponents by 
becoming more powerful than he already is.

70
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:51,840
His opponents are tough, 
too. They don't give up.

71
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,540
Very impressive.

72
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:55,910
Both sides are quite something.

73
00:05:59,790 --> 00:06:01,750
Marvelous...

74
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,410
I'd forgotten.

75
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:08,850
That guy's a blockhead, but when it comes 
to fighting, his mind is a steel trap.

76
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:11,350
Wonderful parfum, Natsu-kun...

77
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:15,060
Damn, how strong is that guy?

78
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,920
H-He's strong...

79
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,630
That's Natsu!

80
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:24,160
But where did Gajeel go?!

81
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,990
I'm scared of what'll happen 
when he comes back...

82
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,670
Hey, is this for real?!

83
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:40,480
I have no memory of seeing the power of 
the Dragon Force losing ground like this.

84
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:43,590
Power, eh?

85
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:52,150
Sting-kun!

86
00:06:52,590 --> 00:06:54,900
Please let me be your disciple!

87
00:06:55,610 --> 00:07:00,290
I saw your fight before! 
I wanna get strong, too!

88
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:03,640
Aren't you scared of me?

89
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:07,130
I'm not scared!

90
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:09,400
I wanna get strong!

91
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:14,840
A cat disciple?

92
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:18,120
Well, whatever. Follow me.

93
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,500
Sting-kun...

94
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,970
Sting!

95
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,990
Yeah!

96
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:46,210
This feeling... The quality of 
the magic has changed again.

97
00:07:46,770 --> 00:07:49,820
The magic of those two has begun to merge.

98
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:54,850
In the end, I wasn't able to get strong,

99
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:58,120
but I love watching strong Sting-kun!

100
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,920
Unison Raid!

101
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:05,080
Their will, breathing, and magic

102
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:07,420
have combined perfectly into one power.

103
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:09,630
But...

104
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:12,070
Natsu! Dodge!

105
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:14,530
Rogue, hang in there!

106
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:16,300
Sting-kun...

107
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,510
Sting-kun, you're the strongest!

108
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:24,600
There are walls that power 
alone can't break through...

109
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:36,710
Natsu!

110
00:08:36,710 --> 00:08:39,100
Yajima-san, what the heck is that?!

111
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:43,680
Unison Raid. It's so-called Uniting Magic.

112
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:48,220
It's high level magic that 
in general can't be mastered

113
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:51,210
even if you devote your whole life to it.

114
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:54,120
This is the power of the Twin Dragons...

115
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,470
However...

116
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:58,690
Holy Shadow Dragon Fang Flash!

117
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:06,240
He's not moving! He intends to take it?!

118
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,480
Natsu!

119
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:11,920
Happy, is something wrong?

120
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,220
You here to see him off?

121
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:15,360
I'm gonna head out.

122
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,750
Not especially...

123
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:19,450
Really? Then I'll see ya later!

124
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:23,230
I'm not gonna say anything!

125
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:26,680
I'm not gonna say anything!

126
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,170
Yeah.

127
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:33,240
I got it...

128
00:09:33,820 --> 00:09:34,790
...partner.

129
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:58,200
It's Fiore's strongest guild, Sabertooth, vs.

130
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:01,470
the strongest guild seven 
years ago, Fairy Tail!

131
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:04,900
And taking the challenge of this 
tag battle are four dragons!

132
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:07,200
Although one of them has 
gone off somewhere...

133
00:10:07,570 --> 00:10:10,000
Currently, below the arena,

134
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,040
Natsu and the Twin Dragons 
are locked in fierce battle!

135
00:10:13,630 --> 00:10:15,350
It's become quiet...

136
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:19,080
No... I feel a strange pressure.

137
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,420
You too?

138
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:21,280
Yeah.

139
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:23,180
Maybe this is...

140
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:26,730
Yo. How do you feel?

141
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:30,570
I'm okay. Is your match next?

142
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,840
Yeah.

143
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:34,190
And I'll win it for sure.

144
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:36,040
Natsu...

145
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:39,290
I believe in you.

146
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:42,950
I have ever since I joined the guild.

147
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,590
Thanks. Leave this to me!

148
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:50,650
What are you talking about, 
"pressure"? That's pathetic!

149
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,570
You're just insensitive!

150
00:10:52,570 --> 00:10:54,640
What are you two doing, a 
husband-and-wife comedy routine?!

151
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,290
We ain't married!

152
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:59,270
No matter how far away he is,

153
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:02,520
he'll always be watching over me...

154
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,400
Look at this.

155
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:17,480
You're surrounded by such good children...

156
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,990
...Makarov.

157
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:24,990
There are walls that can't be 
broken through power alone.

158
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:29,840
But if there is a power that 
can break through those walls,

159
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:31,160
it's...

160
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,420
Holy Shadow Dragon Fang Flash!

161
00:11:39,310 --> 00:11:40,880
...the power of feelings!

162
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:42,780
Secret Dragon Slayer Art!

163
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:47,630
Crimson Lotus Exploding Flame Edge!

164
00:11:53,990 --> 00:11:57,860
Oh, my! It looks like the mega-moves 
of both sides ended the match...

165
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:00,360
It's like an earthquake here!

166
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:03,740
Apparently, the live feed lacrima is 
experiencing technical difficulties,

167
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:06,020
so please sit tight a little longer!

168
00:12:08,110 --> 00:12:09,800
I don't feel any magic...

169
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,870
Meaning it's settled...?

170
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:19,890
Oh, my! Thank you for your patience!

171
00:12:19,890 --> 00:12:22,800
It seems Lacrima-Vision is back up!

172
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:27,960
Natsu Dragneel...

173
00:12:28,890 --> 00:12:33,160
Your power is... immeasurable...

174
00:12:36,290 --> 00:12:37,580
Lector...

175
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,820
He's too strong...

176
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:42,900
Natsu-san...

177
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:45,640
Th-This is...

178
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:50,130
The last one standing is Natsu Dragneel!

179
00:12:52,850 --> 00:12:56,700
A guild is a place that nurtures feelings.

180
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:04,480
It's Fairy Tail! He broke the Twin Dragons!

181
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:08,720
The winner is Fairy Tail!

182
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:11,380
With this, they've leaped to first place!

183
00:13:11,890 --> 00:13:15,790
And this brings an end to the fourth 
day of the Grand Magic Games!

184
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:20,000
After one day off, we'll be back the day 
after tomorrow with the final battle!

185
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,530
The last day...

186
00:13:22,980 --> 00:13:25,590
...will feature a survival battle, 
with all of the members participating!

187
00:13:25,990 --> 00:13:28,740
Which guild will achieve victory in the end?!

188
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:31,330
Don't anyone miss it!

189
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:37,290
I figured it would turn out like this!

190
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:40,500
That's what I expected, 
I guess I should say...

191
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:44,010
Our goal for the final day has changed!

192
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:46,350
Bring it!

193
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:49,900
Defeat Fairy Tail!

194
00:13:50,710 --> 00:13:52,900
You're mine, Gray!

195
00:13:53,310 --> 00:13:56,780
Laxus... Makarov-dono's grandchild...

196
00:13:57,790 --> 00:13:58,740
Erza...

197
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:00,730
Gajeel...

198
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,440
Let's have some fun, Natsu-kun...

199
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:09,440
Lector...

200
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:18,520
I can't believe those two lost...

201
00:14:20,570 --> 00:14:22,540
It was an interesting match.

202
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:25,170
I've thoroughly memorized it.

203
00:14:26,730 --> 00:14:29,520
This'll keep us in the spotlight for a while.

204
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:34,590
"For a while"... If they have a while...

205
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,410
Th-That guy...

206
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:39,480
Saber's master!

207
00:14:47,770 --> 00:14:50,370
The power of feelings, eh?

208
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:55,550
Go ahead. I'll give this match to you.

209
00:14:56,660 --> 00:14:59,240
After this one, we're 
gonna keep winning anyway.

210
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,700
We're not gonna miss one or two points.

211
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:07,070
Don't cry about that one point later, kid!

212
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,730
Let's fight again sometime!

213
00:15:21,570 --> 00:15:22,930
Total defeat...

214
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:28,980
If Gajeel has the same 
fighting strength as Natsu...

215
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:34,670
Just how arrogant am I?

216
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,970
You did it, Natsu!

217
00:15:39,970 --> 00:15:42,480
I gotta hurry up and tell Lucy!

218
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:44,620
You did it, Natsu!

219
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,790
Yeah, well...

220
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:49,400
Today, I'll give you honest praise, Natsu.

221
00:15:50,010 --> 00:15:51,740
You're incredible.

222
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:52,900
R-Really?

223
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,310
Don't be modest!

224
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:59,340
You gave us a good show, but 
what happened to Gajeel?!

225
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,430
Come to think of it...

226
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:06,400
He took off during the middle of it! Doesn't 
he know the meaning of "tag battle"?!

227
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:10,100
Have you forgotten what you did?!

228
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,860
That's Natsu!

229
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:17,190
Get plenty of rest tomorrow to prepare 
for the final day's survival battle.

230
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,540
The final battle, huh?

231
00:16:19,810 --> 00:16:22,040
I'm gonna win it for sure!

232
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:24,030
Victory first!

233
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:26,850
After that, I'm gonna fight 
you two, Erza and Gray!

234
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:29,210
Fine with me.

235
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:32,270
I think you're putting the horse 
before the carriage or whatever...

236
00:16:40,580 --> 00:16:41,880
Good job!

237
00:16:42,190 --> 00:16:43,890
Aren't you gonna ask how it turned out?

238
00:16:44,590 --> 00:16:46,170
I already said, remember?

239
00:16:46,170 --> 00:16:49,930
I've believed in you since 
I first joined the guild.

240
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:54,030
But it ain't over.

241
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,890
This is just the beginning.

242
00:16:56,820 --> 00:17:00,040
Our aim is winning, right?

243
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,930
Of course! We've made it this far.

244
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:06,460
Although we were off to a rotten start 
in last place on the first day...

245
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:08,390
We were even booed then.

246
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:11,370
And laughed at and we got frustrated.

247
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:13,960
But now we're one step away from victory!

248
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,800
Like Natsu said...

249
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:19,410
We're gonna turn it around from zero!

250
00:17:19,660 --> 00:17:23,390
He said to save our tears for when we win!

251
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:27,060
That's right! Let's climb to the top!

252
00:17:27,530 --> 00:17:30,270
"Give up" ain't in our vocabulary!

253
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:33,890
Aim for the 30 million jewel!

254
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:35,560
That's not what it's about!

255
00:17:37,970 --> 00:17:41,090
Let's aim to be the number 
one guild in Fiore!

256
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:43,620
Yeah!

257
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:47,610
A lot's happened since I joined the guild,

258
00:17:48,420 --> 00:17:50,720
but I'm so glad I did!

259
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:54,750
This is what Fairy Tail is about!

260
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,860
Dammit...

261
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:40,940
Salamander... You're dead...

262
00:19:41,530 --> 00:19:46,280
Anyway, where the hell am I? Under the arena?

263
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:52,080
Wha...

264
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,960
What the hell is this?!

265
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:57,780
A dragon... graveyard?!

266
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:02,340
Jellal, what's happening?

267
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:05,000
Don't tell me he got away again?

268
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:09,390
No. I put some distance 
between us, and I'm on his trail.

269
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:12,300
I'm thinking I'll make my move where 
there aren't any other people around.

270
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:13,890
Roger.

271
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,180
You're not getting away this time...

272
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,490
You possess magic similar to Zeref's...

273
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,770
Who the hell are you?!

274
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:26,440
So Sabertooth's been defeated...

275
00:20:27,110 --> 00:20:28,500
...by Natsu-sama...

276
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:33,410
You must have mixed 
feelings, Sergeant Yukino.

277
00:20:33,410 --> 00:20:37,450
No. I no longer feel any 
attachment to the guild.

278
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:42,420
That aside, I just can't get used 
to being addressed as "Sergeant".

279
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:44,880
My apologies.

280
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:48,230
Participating in the Eclipse Project...

281
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:52,450
...requires a temporary rank.

282
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:55,530
The Eclipse Project...

283
00:20:56,710 --> 00:21:01,410
If my power may be of use, then I'm 
prepared to wield it to the utmost.

284
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:06,940
For the sake of Arcadios-sama, 
too, who invited me to join.

285
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:10,920
I suppose I should refer to him as "Colonel".

286
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:12,480
That's all right.

287
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,580
I call him "Captain" myself.

288
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:19,240
And his old friends call him "Dio".

289
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,820
Really?

290
00:21:21,940 --> 00:21:25,010
But he's socially awkward, isn't he?

291
00:21:26,270 --> 00:21:28,580
Even though he's trying to save the world,

292
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:31,400
no one is aware of it...

293
00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:42,720
Is something wrong, Carla?

294
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:44,280
No...

295
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:49,280
Again, that premonition 
of the castle in ruins...

296
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:51,710
Lu-chan, he did it, huh?!

297
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,030
Levy-chan!

298
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:55,020
How are you two doing?

299
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,210
We brought you a present!

300
00:21:57,210 --> 00:22:00,700
If we keep it up, we might 
actually win this thing!

301
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:04,670
Naturally! There's no way 
those members can lose!

302
00:22:04,670 --> 00:22:08,460
Yeah, right?! After seeing today's battle...

303
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:11,740
...I can't even imagine us losing!

304
00:22:12,190 --> 00:22:14,480
By the way, have you seen Gajeel?

305
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,620
Huh? Now that you mention it...

306
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:19,820
He hasn't come back yet?

307
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:22,810
I bet he's off chowin' 
down on iron somewhere.

308
00:22:23,090 --> 00:22:24,980
He'll be back sooner or later.

309
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:26,510
Yeah.

310
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:35,280
That day, we believed in victory.

311
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:39,380
The final day was a really 
hard-fought battle.

312
00:22:40,540 --> 00:22:43,180
Do you remember it, Lu-chan?

313
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,280
And then...

314
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:48,950
...July 7th.

315
00:22:50,420 --> 00:22:55,190
We lost... to fate.

316
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:05,260
That person died...

317
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:09,740
That one, too... Even though I loved...

318
00:23:14,710 --> 00:23:16,490
I can't express in words...

319
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,330
Lu-chan...

320
00:23:19,670 --> 00:23:21,000
I can't take it anymore...

321
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,140
Somebody, help me!

322
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:31,170
Halt!

323
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:37,520
I'm revealing my identity. 
Now you reveal yours.

324
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:45,960
A woman...

325
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,230
It can't be...

326
00:24:05,870 --> 00:24:07,850
Thank you, everyone!

327
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:09,090
Let's meet again!

